title: EJ Manuel, not Tyrod Taylor, to start at quarterback for Bills vs. Bengals
text:
EJ Manuel, not Tyrod Taylor, to start at quarterback for Bills vs. Bengals Resize Text By Matt Bonesteel October 17 at 2:59 PM Follow @MattBonesteel (Getty Images) 
Buffalo Bills quarterback Tyrod Taylor gave it a shot this week in practice, but it looks as if EJ Manuel will get the start Saturday against the Cincinnati Bengals: Sources: EJ Manuel expected to start for @buffalobills tomorrow vs Bengals. Tyrod Taylor (knee) tried to convince coaches, but not ready. 
— bob holtzman (@BobHoltzmanESPN) October 17, 2015 
Taylor suffered a sprained MCL on a horse-collar tackle in last weekend’s win over the Tennessee Titans. There were reports earlier this week that he could miss multiple games because of the injury, and that the Bills were checking the passport status of possible backups with a trip to London looming next weekend. 
Manuel, who lost the Bills’ quarterback competition to Taylor in training camp, received most of the reps with the first-team offense during practice this week. He has started 14 games over his three-year NFL career, with 16 career touchdown passes and 12 interceptions.
